Class SwiftFileStatus

      org.apache.hadoop.fs.swift.snative.SwiftFileStatus
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable, org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable
public class SwiftFileStatus
extends org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileStatus

A subclass of FileStatus that contains the Swift-specific rules of when a file is considered to be a directory.

isDir

public boolean isDir()
Declare that the path represents a directory, which in the SwiftNativeFileSystem means "is a directory or a 0 byte file"

Overrides:
isDir in class org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileStatus
Returns:
true if the status is considered to be a file

isFile

public boolean isFile()
A entry is a file if it is not a directory. By implementing it and not marking as an override this subclass builds and runs in both Hadoop versions.

Overrides:
isFile in class org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileStatus
